Azure Resource Manager (ARM) is the deployment and management layer for Azure resources.

ARM enables:

* Resource deployment
* Access control integration
* Tagging
* Policy enforcement
* Template-based infrastructure

For example, a company can deploy an entire environment (VMs, networking, storage) using one ARM template.

A real-life use case is DevOps automation.

Another example is maintaining consistent infrastructure across environments.

ARM centralizes and standardizes Azure resource management.
